    "_postman_id": "041a5899-5f04-4d94-8975-cf6224608716",
    "name": "EduBroadcast API",
    "description": "**Description:**  \nThis collection provides a comprehensive set of endpoints for the **EduBroadcast Platform,** a specialized MERN-stack application designed for synchronized educational content delivery.\n\nThe system is built on a high-performance architecture that replaces traditional server-side timers with a mathematical **Modulo Rotation Engine**, ensuring perfectly synchronized live broadcasts across all clients.\n\n---\n\n### **🛠 Core Modules**\n\n- **Identity & Access Management:** Secure registration and `HttpOnly` cookie-based JWT authentication.\n    \n- **Teacher Workflow:** Robust media uploading with strict 10MB size limits and subject-based scheduling.\n    \n- **Principal Governance:** Administrative oversight with a full pending-queue approval/rejection system.\n    \n- **Live Broadcast Engine:** A public-facing, stateless API that calculates real-time playback positions across subjects.\n    \n\n---\n\n### **🚀 Getting Started**\n\n1. **Environment Setup:** Ensure you have the `EduBroadcast Local` (or `Production`) environment selected in the top-right corner.\n    \n2. **Variable Injection:** This collection uses `{{baseUrl}}` for all requests. By default, this is set to `http://localhost:3000`.\n    \n3. **Authentication Flow:** - Start by registering a user or logging in with existing credentials (`t1@gmail.com` or `p1@gmail.com`).\n    \n    - Postman will automatically handle the session cookies—no manual token pasting is required.\n        \n4. **Testing Uploads:** Use the `upload content` request to test the **Multer Firewall**. Try a file over 10MB to see the error-handling in action.\n    \n\n---\n\n### **⚖️ Status Codes**\n\n- `200 OK` / `201 Created`: Request successful.\n    \n- `400 Bad Request`: Validation error (e.g., File too large, missing fields).\n    \n- `401 Unauthorized`: Missing or invalid session cookie.\n    \n- `403 Forbidden`: Role mismatch (e.g., a Teacher trying to access Principal endpoints).\n    \n- `500 Internal Server Error`: Unexpected server-side failure.\n    \n\n---\n\n**Developed by:** Ashutosh Raj",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
